Anonymous Thu 30 Aug 2018 06:13:44 No.17983103 Report
Quoted By: >>17983174 >>17983176 >>17983188 >>17984334 >>17985202
>>17982776
I'm not sure why that anon is insisting on it, but personally I could support the idea to use an unnamed-yet-not MC who uses is referred to with a title or something. People instantly form a myriad of preconceived notions from MC's name. For example, imagine if someone wrote a story and the MC's name was Miguel or Jamal. /hmofa/ would burn for weeks.
If a writefag wanted to do as they please freely, they could name their characters whatever they desired. Make of them what they please. When you write for an audience (for example /hmofa/) you must take care to, if not cater enthusiastically to said audience, not offend them.

Related, giving MC's particularly self-insertion hindering traits and history should be avoided. There is a reason most stories here avoid digging into the MC's past before the story begins. Family, while not taboo, can hinder self-insertion. A lot of MC's, mine included, tend to suffer from lot from abandoned only child syndrome. There is no one else immediately relevant to the MC, and it's just accepted to the point where I've literally never seen anyone go "Why doesn't Anon know anybody other than Ariannis?" Everybody just rolled with it. It's part of the appeal, akin to just popping a quarter into the machine and starting a round of pinball. As the writer, I don't have to waste energy and effort with an elaborate backstory, and in fact am encouraged not to disrupt the reader's experience. It's not what they came here for.

That being said, this approach of trying to not bag down the reader results in shallow literature. However here in /hmofa/, simple smut is expected, not works worthy of a spot on New York Time's best seller's list. It's alright to play in the puddles if you don't delude yourself into thinking it'll make you an Olympic swimmer one day. God knows that there isn't enough red ink in a pack of pens to grade every /hmofa/ green.
Just like, write smut my dudes. Good smut though. Hold yourself to a standard, please.
